{"filter":false,"title":"faq-mq.php","tooltip":"/careers/faq-mq.php","undoManager":{"mark":14,"position":14,"stack":[[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":34,"column":27},"end":{"row":34,"column":54},"action":"remove","lines":[" Frequently Asked Questions"]},{"start":{"row":34,"column":27},"end":{"row":34,"column":87},"action":"insert","lines":["10 things that you need to know about IBMâ€™s new MQ Appliance"]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":60,"column":27},"end":{"row":60,"column":83},"action":"remove","lines":[" What sort of qualities do we look for in our employees?"]},{"start":{"row":60,"column":27},"end":{"row":60,"column":88},"action":"insert","lines":["What capabilities does the appliance have in terms of memory?"]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":63,"column":27},"end":{"row":64,"column":28},"action":"remove","lines":[" At Miracle we believe in hard working and motivated individuals, and in turn take those qualities into consideration when we go searching for our employees. Anybody who is great working in teams, has great passing towards IT and a hard working attitude will be a perfect fit and a instant hit in our organization.","                        </p>"]},{"start":{"row":63,"column":27},"end":{"row":63,"column":519},"action":"insert","lines":["The MQ Appliance has 2 on-board discs, which adds up to about 1 TB of usable memory for your messages on each disc which is RAID enabled for replication of 1 disc on to the RAID copy disc. SSD and Flash based memory is not available on the appliance due to the heavy writing load that is expected with a messaging appliance. Higher amounts of storage for logging data can be provided using fiber channels. The appliance also only supports circular logging but does not support linear logging."]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":63,"column":519},"end":{"row":64,"column":0},"action":"insert","lines":["",""]},{"start":{"row":64,"column":0},"end":{"row":64,"column":27},"action":"insert","lines":["                           "]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":64,"column":26},"end":{"row":64,"column":27},"action":"remove","lines":[" "]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":64,"column":25},"end":{"row":64,"column":26},"action":"remove","lines":[" "]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":64,"column":24},"end":{"row":64,"column":25},"action":"remove","lines":[" "]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":64,"column":24},"end":{"row":64,"column":25},"action":"insert","lines":["<"]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":64,"column":25},"end":{"row":64,"column":26},"action":"insert","lines":["/"]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":64,"column":26},"end":{"row":64,"column":27},"action":"insert","lines":["p"]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":64,"column":27},"end":{"row":64,"column":28},"action":"insert","lines":[">"]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":71,"column":27},"end":{"row":71,"column":81},"action":"remove","lines":[" What sort of technologies do our employees work with?"]},{"start":{"row":71,"column":27},"end":{"row":71,"column":73},"action":"insert","lines":["What are the pricing models for the appliance?"]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":74,"column":27},"end":{"row":74,"column":369},"action":"remove","lines":[" We have always been a specialist in niche IT spaces and are known for our fluency with IBM products. Our technical teams get a chance to play with some of the latest technologies from software giants such as IBM, SAP, Oracle, Amazon and more while also being given a chance to check out some of the upcoming Open Source Technologies as well."]},{"start":{"row":74,"column":27},"end":{"row":74,"column":393},"action":"insert","lines":["The MQ Appliance comes in 2 physical form factors, the MQ M2000 A and the MQ M2000 B. Both the appliances consist of the same features in terms of deployment, security and messaging. The major difference between the low-cost M2000 B and the high-cost M2000 A is the number of processor cores, which means that the workload capability is reduced for the B appliance. "]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":82,"column":27},"end":{"row":82,"column":91},"action":"remove","lines":[" What will be the duration and contents of our training program?"]},{"start":{"row":82,"column":27},"end":{"row":82,"column":81},"action":"insert","lines":[" Can applications and agents be run on a MQ Appliance?"]}]}],[{"group":"doc","deltas":[{"start":{"row":85,"column":27},"end":{"row":85,"column":399},"action":"remove","lines":[" The training for our IT Gurukulam Program is for 3 months, starting with 3 days of induction, 1 week of Database Training, and 2 weeks of intensive Java and J2EE training. Once the Core Training(45 days) is completed the trainee will be thoroughly evaluated and then placed into an appropriate technology space where they will be trained for 45 days on a speciality tool."]},{"start":{"row":85,"column":27},"end":{"row":85,"column":542},"action":"insert","lines":["No, Applications cannot be run (or) deployed on a MQ Appliance. The appliance follows a Hub Pattern, which means that any application that wants to connect to the appliance must connect as a remote client. It is not possible to run agents such as MQ agents, MFT agents and monitoring agents as well on the appliance and they must all be used as remote clients to ensure messaging, file transfer and monitoring capabilities. This ensures that the workload of the appliance is all allocated to the messaging aspects. "]}]}]]},"ace":{"folds":[],"scrolltop":900,"scrollleft":104,"selection":{"start":{"row":85,"column":542},"end":{"row":85,"column":542},"isBackwards":false},"options":{"guessTabSize":true,"useWrapMode":false,"wrapToView":true},"firstLineState":{"row":64,"state":"start","mode":"ace/mode/php"}},"timestamp":1427370697049,"hash":"eaa72ac989abb2a18773d4720dd5eaf6e65edf24"}